#29005
#PRavyn's Glade.#n~
As you cross the room's threshold, you have to wonder if you are 
still inside.  The stonewalls follow from the hallway into this room, 
however a few feet inside they become covered with ivy, and beautiful 
exotic flowers.  The walls extend upward about thirty feet before they 
seem to seamlessly blend into a brilliant star light sky.  The grass 
becomes taller the deeper into the room you venture.  You also notice 
the air grows cool and moist, you can even feel the light breeze from 
the north blow across your face.  The rustling of leaves catches your 
attention, and as you look up you behold the most breathtaking vision 
you have ever seen.  Silhouetted against a full moon a huge tree sits 
atop a small rise.  The purple leaves shimmer as they gently blow in the 
breeze.  As you follow the trunk down to the base, you behold a Throne...
carved into the tree itself.  No mortal craftsmen could of created such 
an impressive artifact.  At closer examination you discover that the 
Throne was grown...it is part of the tree itself.  Gaia herself is at 
work here.  A light mist hangs around the base of the tree, as you 
approach closer, and in the distance the soulful howls of wolves echo.
~
